    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Creative Commons"@fr, "Creative Commons"@en, "Creative Commons"@ro, "Creative Commons"@hu, "Creative Commons"@sv, "Creative Commons"@hr, "Creative Commons"@es, "Creative Commons"@lt, "Creative Commons"@pl, "Creative Commons"@ga, "Creative Commons"@de, "Creative Commons"@el, "Creative Commons"@sl, "Creative Commons"@nl, "Creative Commons"@pt, "Creative Commons"@cs, "Creative Commons"@lv, "Creative Commons"@fi, "Creative Commons"@sk, "Creative Commons"@it, "Creative Commons"@et, "Creative Commons"@mt, "Creative Commons"@da, "Криейтив Комънс"@bg;
    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Creative Commons is a global nonprofit organization that enables sharing and reuse of creativity and knowledge through the provision of free legal tools.It is led by a Board of Directors comprised of thought leaders, education experts, technologists, legal scholars, investors, entrepreneurs and philanthropists. CC legal tools help those who want to encourage reuse of their works by offering them for use under generous, standardized terms; those who want to make creative uses of works; and those who want to benefit from this symbiosis."@en;
