    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "The Latin American and the Caribbean Economic System is an organization founded to promote economic cooperation and social development between Latin American and the Caribbean countries. Its representatives consist of members from 28 countries and took part in the General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade (GATT) negotiations."@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#notation> "COB0001072"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#XML_RECORD>, "LACES"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#LAC>, "LACES"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#NAC>;
